me.joeycumines.javapromises.core

Class PromiseTest

  • java.lang.Object
    • me.joeycumines.javapromises.core.PromiseTest
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    PromiseRunnableTest, PromiseStageTest

    public abstract class PromiseTest
extends java.lang.Object
    Extend this class to test a Promise implementation.

    It requires a PromiseFactory instance to work, so you will have to implement that as well. You probably want to extend PromiseApi as the base, and implement PromiseApiTest, as well.

      • testGetState

        public void testGetState()
        Test Promise.getState()

        --------------------------------------------

        Get the current state of the promise.

        A promise's initial state is PENDING, will change at most once, to either resolved states, FULFILLED or REJECTED.

        @return The state of the promise.

      • testThenCallbackReturnNull

        public void testThenCallbackReturnNull()
        Test Promise.then(Function)

        --------------------------------------------

        If the callback returns a null value, then the returned promise will resolve as FULFILLED with value null.

      • testExceptCallbackDoesNothingOnFulfill

        public void testExceptCallbackDoesNothingOnFulfill()
        Test Promise.except(Function) and Promise.except(BiConsumer)

        --------------------------------------------

        If this resolved with the FULFILLED state, then the returned promise will reflect the state and value of this, and the callback will not be run.
